Chapter 2. Who can take it

This course is designed for anyone who wants to learn how to analyze data with Python. No prior experience with Python or data analysis is required.

The course is divided into three parts:

* Part 1: Getting started with Python and the Jupyter Notebook.
* Part 2: Reading, cleaning, and transforming data with pandas.
* Part 3: Analyzing and visualizing data with pandas and matplotlib.

Each part includes a series of interactive tutorials that will teach you the basics of Python and pandas. You will also learn how to use the Jupyter Notebook to publish your analysis.

At the end of the course, you will be able to:

* Read data from a CSV file into a pandas DataFrame.
* Clean and transform data using pandas DataFrame methods.
* Analyze data using pandas DataFrame methods.
* Visualize data using matplotlib.
* Publish your analysis using Jupyter.

